<TITLE> RAB recover 'valuable' touchstone statue of Krishna in Jatrabari </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Feb 23 (bdnews24.com)-The Rapid Action Battalion recovered a valuable 'touchstone statue' of Lord Krishna from the capital's Jatrabari area Friday, RAB officials said Saturday. At a press conference at RAB-2's offices in Dhaka, the elite force said the statue was valued at Tk one crore. Suspected smugglers, Haji Tuhin Khan (27) and Biswajit Banik Billu (29), were arrested at the time, RAB-2 officials said. The two suspects allegedly confessed that the statue was smuggled from India to Habiganj district, and later brought to Jatrabari in Dhaka, the officials said in their statement. The two arrestees, of a village in Habiganj, were handed over to Jatrabari police. A senior RAB official told bdnews24.com: "A team of RAB-2 acting on a tip off recovered the statue of Lord Krishna under the guise of buyers." The statue was recovered from North Jatrabari Friday noon, he said. The 12 kg statue is thought to be about 250 years old, and its value estimated at Tk one crore, he added. A case has been filed in this connection, police said. bdnews
